******
[3] Cholera - Uganda (Amuru District)
Date: Tue 18 Oct 2016
Source: AllAfrica, The Observer report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201610190681.html


The 3 cholera patients admitted for treatment at St Mary's Hospital Lacor in Gulu have been discharged from isolation. Dr Emmanuel Ochola, the head of HIV, research and documentation department says the hospital effectively contained the disease within days and no new cases have emerged.

Dr Ochola says the 3 left the isolation ward on Fri 14 Oct 2016 after fully recovering from the disease. They were residents of Bibiya village in Elegu parish, Atiak sub-county in Amuru district. The 3 were brought from the outskirts of South Sudan refugees' reception centres on Elegu border post where the ministry of Health has been battling an outbreak since September 2016.

As many as 2 of the victims were members of the same family while the 3rd was a 14-year-old boy who reported to the hospital while already on treatment. Dr Ochola urged communities to practice proper waste disposal and observe high standard of hygiene to prevent further outbreak.

